      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAKIE SMOKESHOW (2) copped the outside barrier when resuming last week so was far from disgraced when midfield. Much better served by this barrier and he showed some strong form last campaign. Has recorded a win and a placing in two previous second-up attempts so expect big improvement. MONTEFIORE NZ (3) could be close to a win after coming from wider to place in two of his last three outings here, beaten just 1.4m last week. Should get his chance from this barrier. RIVERA LOU (9) may need some luck from the wide draw but could be close to a win following back-to-back placings. PETES CRUNCH TIME (4) is another drawn lower than last week and there was merit in that effort when beaten only 3.2m into fourth. BARTELLO (7) draws wider but showed improvement to place last week and should be fitter again third up.",
